data.name: Oatmeal Waffles
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously fluffy waffles made with wholesome oats, perfect for breakfast or a snack.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat your waffle iron according to the manufacturer's instructions.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the rolled oats and milk. Let it sit for about 5 minutes to soften the oats.
Add the egg, baking powder, vanilla extract, maple syrup, melted coconut oil, and salt to the bowl. Mix until well combined.
Lightly grease the waffle iron with cooking spray or a little coconut oil.
Pour the batter onto the preheated waffle iron, using about 1/2 cup of batter for each waffle (adjust according to your waffle iron's size).
Close the lid and cook until the waffles are golden brown and cooked through, about 3-5 minutes.
Carefully remove the waffles and repeat with the remaining batter.
Serve warm with your favorite toppings like fresh fruit, yogurt, or more maple syrup.
